{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.18",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 18 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:1",
      "text": "He that liveth for ever created all things together. God only shall be justified, and he remaineth an invincible king for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:2",
      "text": "Who is able to declare his works?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:3",
      "text": "For who shall search out his glorious acts?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:4",
      "text": "And who shall show forth the power of his majesty? or who shall be able to declare his mercy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:5",
      "text": "Nothing may be taken away, nor added, neither is it possible to find out the glorious works of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:6",
      "text": "When a man hath done, then shall he begin: and when he leaveth off, he shall be at a loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:7",
      "text": "What is man, and what is his grace? and what is his good, or what is his evil?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:8",
      "text": "The number of the days of men at the most are a hundred years, as a drop of water of the sea are they esteemed: and as a pebble of the sand, so are a few years compared to eternity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:9",
      "text": "Therefore God is patient in them, and poureth forth his mercy upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:10",
      "text": "He hath seen the presumption of their heart that it is wicked, and hath known their end that it is evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:11",
      "text": "Therefore hath he filled up his mercy in their favour, and hath shewn them the way of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:12",
      "text": "The compassion of man is toward his neighbour: but the mercy of God is upon all flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:13",
      "text": "He hath mercy, and teacheth, and correcteth, as a shepherd doth his flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:14",
      "text": "He hath mercy on him that receiveth the discipline of mercy, and that maketh haste in his judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:15",
      "text": "My son, in thy good deeds, make no complaint, and when thou givest any thing, add not grief by an evil word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:16",
      "text": "Shall not the dew assuage the heat? so also the good word is better than the gift.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:17",
      "text": "Lo, is not a word better than a gift? but both are with a justified man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:18",
      "text": "A fool will upbraid bitterly: and a gift of one ill taught consumeth the eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:19",
      "text": "Before judgment prepare thee justice, and learn before thou speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:20",
      "text": "Before sickness take a medicine, and before judgment examine thyself, and thou shalt find mercy in the sight of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:21",
      "text": "Humble thyself before thou art sick, and in the time of sickness shew thy conversation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:22",
      "text": "Let nothing hinder thee from praying always, and be not afraid to be justified even to death: for the reward of God continueth for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:23",
      "text": "Before prayer prepare thy soul: and be not as a man that tempteth God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:24",
      "text": "Remember the wrath that shall be at the last day, and the time of repaying when he shall turn away his face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:25",
      "text": "Remember poverty in the time of abundance, and the necessities of poverty in the day of riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:26",
      "text": "From the morning until the evening the time shall be changed, and all these are swift in the eyes of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:27",
      "text": "A wise man will fear in every thing, and in the days of sins will beware of sloth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:28",
      "text": "Every man of understanding knoweth wisdom, and will give praise to him that findeth her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:29",
      "text": "They that were of good understanding in words, have also done wisely themselves: and have understood truth and justice, and have poured forth proverbs and judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:30",
      "text": "Go not after thy lusts, but turn away from thy own will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:31",
      "text": "If thou give to thy soul her desires, she will make thee a joy to thy enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:32",
      "text": "Take no pleasure in riotous assemblies, be they ever so small: for their concertation is continual.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.18.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 18:33",
      "text": "Make not thyself poor by borrowing to contribute to feasts when thou hast nothing in thy purse: for thou shalt be an enemy to thy own life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
